'''''Closer to Truth''''' is a continuing [[television series]] on public television<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.wgbh.org/programs/Closer-to-Truth-14 |title=Closer to Truth |publisher=Wgbh.org |date= |accessdate=2014-06-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.mptv.org/schedule/a-z/program/closer-to-truth/ |title=Closer to Truth schedule on MPTV |publisher=Mptv.org |date= |accessdate=2014-06-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20141027164202/http://www.mptv.org/schedule/a-z/program/closer-to-truth/ |archivedate=2014-10-27 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.cpt12.org/tv_schedule/program_details.cfm?id=220130812220000 |title=Colorado Public Television, Denver PBS, CPT12 (Formerly KBDI) |publisher=Cpt12.org |date= |accessdate=2014-06-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20131202224330/http://www.cpt12.org/tv_schedule/program_details.cfm?id=220130812220000 |archivedate=2013-12-02 |df= }}</ref><ref>{{cite web|url=http://apthd.com/series/1650/Closer-to-Truth/ |title=Closer to Truth on Alabama Public Television |publisher=Apthd.com |date= |accessdate=2014-06-17 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://web.archive.org/web/20140806160151/http://www.apthd.com/series/1650/Closer-to-Truth/ |archivedate=2014-08-06 |df= }}</ref> originally created, produced and hosted by [[Robert Lawrence Kuhn]]. The first premiere series aired in 2000 for 2 seasons, followed by a second series aired in 2003 for a single season. The third series of the program, '''''Closer to Truth: Cosmos. Consciousness. God''''', launched in 2008, with 15 full seasons to date. See [[List of Closer to Truth episodes]]. ''Closer to Truth'' has had over 150,000 station broadcasts.
The show is centered on on-camera conversations with leading scientists, philosophers, theologians, and scholars, covering a diverse range of topics or questions from the [[cause]], size and nature of the universe (or [[multiverse]]), to the mystery of consciousness and the notion of free will, to the existence and essence of God, to the mystery of existence (why is there anything at all).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.kqed.org/tv/programs/index.jsp?pgmid=17540 |title=Closer to Truth &#124; KQED Public Media for Northern CA |publisher=Kqed.org |date= |accessdate=2014-06-17}}</ref><ref name="blogspot1">{{cite web|url=http://scienceandreligiontoday.blogspot.com/2008/09/were-getting-closer-to-truth.html |title=Science & Religion Today: We're Getting "Closer to Truth" |publisher=Scienceandreligiontoday.blogspot.com |date=2008-09-10 |accessdate=2014-06-17}}</ref><ref>{{cite web|author=Luke Muehlhauser |url=http://commonsenseatheism.com/?p=1977 |title=Closer to Truth |publisher=Commonsenseatheism.com |date=2009-06-05 |accessdate=2014-06-17}}</ref>
The ''Closer to Truth'' website features extensive conversations in addition to those that have been broadcast on TV (~4,000 videos).<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.closertotruth.com/about/content-guide |title=Content Guide |publisher=Closer to Truth |date= |accessdate=2014-06-17}}</ref> It is the world’s largest archive of video interviews with leading experts in cosmos (philosophy of cosmology/physics), consciousness (philosophy of religion), meaning (philosophy of religion) - www.closertotruth.com.
Robert Lawrence Kuhn is the creator, executive producer, writer and presenter of the series.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.choprafoundation.org/speakers/robert-kuhn/ |title=Robert Lawrence Kuhn « The Chopra Foundation |publisher=Choprafoundation.org |date= |accessdate=2014-06-17}}</ref> Peter Getzels is the co-creator, producer and director.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.bethesdamagazine.com/Bethesda-Magazine/September-October-2013/Peter-Getzels/ |title=Reel Life - Bethesda Magazine - September-October 2013 - Bethesda, MD |publisher=Bethesda Magazine |date= |accessdate=2014-06-17}}</ref><ref>https://www.imdb.com/name/nm2011631/</ref>
